---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Affiliate Programs by Niche: Find the Right Fit Faster";
const description = "Find affiliate programs by niche and connect your topic focus with more relevant monetization options.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 border-b border-gray-800">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-400">If you already know your niche, this page helps you narrow down the types of affiliate programs that fit more naturally.</p>
      <div class="mt-10">
        <a href="#compare" class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">Match your niche to the right offers</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Choosing the right option is harder than it looks.</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4">You already know what you want to write about. But many people focus on the wrong signal first—such as choosing a popular program before verifying if it matches the niche audience's real intent. This leads to a disconnect between content workflow and conversion workflow.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">A better choice usually comes down to fit:</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-2 mb-8">
        <li>does the commission model match the niche's buying habits?</li>
        <li>what are competitors successfully promoting?</li>
        <li>how your audience buys within this space</li>
        <li>is this easier to integrate natively into your content?</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">What You’ll Find on This Page</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">Instead of forcing one monetization path, you can explore the options that align better with how you already create content. This page is designed to map common niches to their best-fit affiliate paths.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Who This Is For</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4">This page is a good fit if you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>already know your specific niche focus</li>
        <li>already have content but want better monetization that seamlessly fits</li>
        <li>need a direct route from broad topics to specific <a href="/programs" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">programs</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">This may be less useful if you’re still deciding between multiple foundational topics. In that case, check out our <a href="/offers/find-your-best-affiliate-fit" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">best-fit routing page</a> first.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Why This Direction Matters</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">Instead of trying to force high-ticket software on an impulse-buying lifestyle audience, or low-ticket Amazon items on B2B SaaS traffic, you can align perfectly with users' intent.</p>

      <h2 id="compare" class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Match the Path</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-700 mb-8">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you write about B2B / SaaS / Software</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Focus heavily on recurring revenue tools and platforms. The volume might be lower, but the retention and long-term customer value are massively higher.</p>
            <a href="/niches" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">Explore B2B niches &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you write about Lifestyle / Travel / Consumer Goods</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Focus on massive consumer affiliate networks or Amazon. The commission percentages are lower, but high traffic volume bridges the gap.</p>
            <a href="/niches" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">Explore consumer niches &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="pb-2">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you write about Finance / Investing</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Focus on high-ticket, high-competition CPA networks. Trust is the absolute key here.</p>
            <a href="/niches" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">Explore finance niches &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Trust & Rationale</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">The goal here is not to label one niche as universally “best.” It’s to help you compare the right variables so you can choose what fits your workflow. A program that works wonders in personal finance will likely fail completely in the pet niche.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-400 text-lg mb-12">
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">What if I’m still unsure about my niche?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Start with the pages that help narrow your direction first. A better fit often becomes clearer once you actually have a core audience to speak to.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">Should I pick my niche based on the highest commission rates?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Usually not. Content creation in a niche you hate just for commission rates leads to rapid burnout. Fit matters more.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">How do I find programs specifically for my niche?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Use our structured indexing or look closely at what competitors are actively promoting inside your niche. Look past surface-level claims.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">What matters more: niche, platform, or offer?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Niche and audience always come first. The platform and the offer exist merely to service the pain points of the niche you have chosen.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-700 text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Find Programs by Niche</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-6">Identify the programs that naturally map to your specific content.</p>
        <a href="/programs" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">Explore niche-based opportunities</a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Related Resources</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-3 mb-8">
        <li><a href="/blog/how-to-choose-a-niche-for-affiliate-marketing" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">How to Choose a Niche for Affiliate Marketing More Clearly</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/from-niche-to-program-match-affiliate-offers" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">From Niche to Program: A Simpler Way to Match Affiliate Offers</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/common-affiliate-marketing-mistakes-beginners-make" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Common Affiliate Marketing Mistakes Beginners Make Early On</a></li>
        <li><a href="/offers/best-affiliate-programs-for-beginners" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Best Affiliate Programs for Beginners</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
